data.description:
1. Israel officially announced a strike against Iran;
2. Trump: Creating a strategic reserve of Bitcoin is not enough, the United States also needs a clear and simple crypto market framework;
3. Gold rose 1.22% during the day, and Bitcoin's intraday decline widened to 2.15%;
4. The U.S. Senate will hold a final vote on the GENIUS Act on June 17;
5. GameStop will increase the size of the convertible priority notes to be privately issued to US$2.25 billion;
6. Coinbase CEO: Congress should pass the CLARITY Act and the GENIUS Act together;
7. BlackRock incorporates crypto assets into the core of its 2030 strategic vision;
8. The Blockchain Group completed 9.7 million euros in financing and increased its Bitcoin vault strategy;
9. U.S. President Trump suggested that the Federal Reserve cut interest rates by 200 basis points;
10. The number of initial jobless claims in the United States rose to the highest level since October last year.
